00067 /* Special defines which change the way the code is built depending on the
00068    CPU and OS.  For SGI machines you can use _MIPS_SZLONG (32 or 64) to find
00069    even newer MIPS CPU's, but at the moment one size fits all for
00070    optimization options.  Older Sparc's work better with only UNROLL, but
00071    there's no way to tell at compile time what it is you're running on */
00072 
00073 #if defined( sun )                    /* Newer Sparc's */
00074 #  define BF_PTR
00075 #elif defined( __ultrix )     /* Older MIPS */
00076 #  define BF_PTR
00077 #elif defined( __osf1__ )     /* Alpha */
00078   /* None */
00079 #elif defined ( _AIX )                /* RS6000 */
00080   /* Unknown */
00081 #elif defined( __hpux )               /* HP-PA */
00082   /* None */
00083 #elif defined( __aux )                /* 68K */
00084   /* Unknown */
00085 #elif defined( __dgux )               /* 88K (but P6 in latest boxes) */
00086   /* Unknown */
00087 #elif defined( __sgi )                /* Newer MIPS */
00088 #  define BF_PTR
00089 #elif defined( i386 )         /* x86 boxes, should be gcc */
00090 #  define BF_PTR2
00091 #elif defined( _MSC_VER )     /* x86 boxes, Visual C */
00092 #  define BF_PTR2
00093 #endif /* Systems-specific speed defines */

00095 #undef c2l
00096 #define c2l(c,l)        (l =((unsigned long)(*((c)++)))    , \
00097                          l|=((unsigned long)(*((c)++)))<< 8L, \
00098                          l|=((unsigned long)(*((c)++)))<<16L, \
00099                          l|=((unsigned long)(*((c)++)))<<24L)

00101 /* NOTE - c is not incremented as per c2l */
00102 #undef c2ln
00103 #define c2ln(c,l1,l2,n) { \
00104                         c+=n; \
00105                         l1=l2=0; \
00106                         switch (n) { \
00107                         case 8: l2 =((unsigned long)(*(--(c))))<<24L; \
00108                         case 7: l2|=((unsigned long)(*(--(c))))<<16L; \
00109                         case 6: l2|=((unsigned long)(*(--(c))))<< 8L; \
00110                         case 5: l2|=((unsigned long)(*(--(c))));     \
00111                         case 4: l1 =((unsigned long)(*(--(c))))<<24L; \
00112                         case 3: l1|=((unsigned long)(*(--(c))))<<16L; \
00113                         case 2: l1|=((unsigned long)(*(--(c))))<< 8L; \
00114                         case 1: l1|=((unsigned long)(*(--(c))));     \
00115                                 } \
00116                         }

00183 /* This is actually a big endian algorithm, the most significate byte
00184  * is used to lookup array 0 */

00186 /* use BF_PTR2 for intel boxes,
00187  * BF_PTR for sparc and MIPS/SGI
00188  * use nothing for Alpha and HP.
00189  */
00190 #if !defined(BF_PTR) && !defined(BF_PTR2)
00191 #define BF_PTR2
00192 #endif

00194 #define BF_M    0x3fc
00195 #define BF_0    22L
00196 #define BF_1    14L
00197 #define BF_2     6L
00198 #define BF_3     2L /* left shift */
00199 
00200 #if defined(BF_PTR2)

00202 /* This is basically a special pentium verson */
00203 #define BF_ENC(LL,R,S,P) \
00204         { \
00205         BF_LONG t,u,v; \
00206         u=R>>BF_0; \
00207         v=R>>BF_1; \
00208         u&=BF_M; \
00209         v&=BF_M; \
00210         t=  *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[  0])+u); \
00211         u=R>>BF_2; \
00212         t+= *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[256])+v); \
00213         v=R<<BF_3; \
00214         u&=BF_M; \
00215         v&=BF_M; \
00216         t^= *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[512])+u); \
00217         LL^=P; \
00218         t+= *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[768])+v); \
00219         LL^=t; \
00220         }
00221 
00222 #elif defined(BF_PTR)
00223 
00224 /* This is normally very good */
00225 
00226 #define BF_ENC(LL,R,S,P) \
00227         LL^=P; \
00228         LL^= (((*(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[  0])+((R>>BF_0)&BF_M))+ \
00229                 *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[256])+((R>>BF_1)&BF_M)))^ \
00230                 *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[512])+((R>>BF_2)&BF_M)))+ \
00231                 *(BF_LONG *)((unsigned char *)&(S[768])+((R<<BF_3)&BF_M)));
00232 #else
00233 
00234 /* This will always work, even on 64 bit machines and strangly enough,
00235  * on the Alpha it is faster than the pointer versions (both 32 and 64
00236  * versions of BF_LONG) */
00237 
00238 #define BF_ENC(LL,R,S,P) \
00239         LL^=P; \
00240         LL^=((( S[        (int)(R>>24L)      ] + \
00241                 S[0x0100+((int)(R>>16L)&0xff)])^ \
00242                 S[0x0200+((int)(R>> 8L)&0xff)])+ \
00243                 S[0x0300+((int)(R     )&0xff)])&0xffffffffL;
00244 #endif
